# Maintainers currently unavailable for auto-assignment.
#
# Add your GitHub username on its own line to stop receiving auto-assigned
# issues and PR reviews; remove the line when you're back. Comments start with
# '#'. Only the first token on each line is read as the username -- any text
# after it is a free-form human note (reason, expected return date, ...) and is
# ignored by the tooling.
#
# Availability only ever NARROWS the candidate pool: if filtering would leave no
# one to assign, the selectors fall back to assigning anyway, so a PR or issue is
# never left unassigned because everyone is out.
#
# Consulted by:
#   - .github/workflows/auto-assign-reviewer.js  (PR reviewer routing)
#   - .github/workflows/issue-triage.yml         (P0/P1 issue round-robin)
#
# username        [free-form note -- e.g. reason / return date]
